      "writtenOn": "2026-03-16T05:31:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How do we know that the maximum chassis will be below 50?\n\nAssuming number of chassis will be less than 50, and assuming all chassis numbers are continuous, I think we can use a compile time fixed size array: \n\n`constexpr auto l_maxNumChassis{50};`\n`std::array\u003cnlohmann::json, l_maxNumChassis \u003e m_chassisJsonArray`\n\n\n\nWe can then use the chassis suffix number from the chassis ID string \"chassisN\", and use N as an index to the respective JSON entry in the array.\n\nAdvantage:\n1. Fixed memory allocated at compile time, no compile time memory allocation operations.\n2. O(1) modification of chassis JSON entry\n3. O(1) look up of chassis JSON entry.",
      "parentUuid": "fd74b31b_cdb8ed2b",
      "revId": "f30e27b7b7f549293b8b5894f4fa737451173766",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
